3/*++
4/* NAME
5/* bounce_notify_util 3
6/* SUMMARY
7/* send non-delivery report to sender, server side
8/* SYNOPSIS
9/* #include "bounce_service.h"
10/*
11/* typedef struct {
12/* .in +4
13/* /* All private members... */
14/* .in -4
15/* } BOUNCE_INFO;
16/*
17/* BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_mail_init(service, queue_name, queue_id, encoding,
18/* smtputf8, dsn_envid, template)
19/* const char *service;
20/* const char *queue_name;
21/* const char *queue_id;
22/* const char *encoding;
23/* int smtputf8;
24/* const char *dsn_envid;
25/* const BOUNCE_TEMPLATE *template;
26/*
27/* BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_mail_one_init(queue_name, queue_id, encoding,
28/* smtputf8, dsn_envid, dsn_notify,
29/* rcpt_buf, dsn_buf, template)
30/* const char *queue_name;
31/* const char *queue_id;
32/* const char *encoding;
33/* int smtputf8;
34/* int dsn_notify;
35/* const char *dsn_envid;
36/* RCPT_BUF *rcpt_buf;
37/* DSN_BUF *dsn_buf;
38/* const BOUNCE_TEMPLATE *template;
39/*
40/* void bounce_mail_free(bounce_info)
41/* BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info;
42/*
43/* int bounce_header(fp, bounce_info, recipient, postmaster_copy)
44/* VSTREAM *fp;
45/* BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info;
46/* const char *recipient;
47/* int postmaster_copy;
48/*
49/* int bounce_boilerplate(fp, bounce_info)
50/* VSTREAM *fp;
51/* BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info;
52/*
53/* int bounce_recipient_log(fp, bounce_info)
54/* VSTREAM *fp;
55/* BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info;
56/*
57/* int bounce_diagnostic_log(fp, bounce_info, notify_filter)
58/* VSTREAM *fp;
59/* BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info;
60/* int notify_filter;
61/*
62/* int bounce_header_dsn(fp, bounce_info)
63/* VSTREAM *fp;
64/* BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info;
65/*
66/* int bounce_recipient_dsn(fp, bounce_info)
67/* VSTREAM *fp;
68/* BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info;
69/*
70/* int bounce_diagnostic_dsn(fp, bounce_info, notify_filter)
71/* VSTREAM *fp;
72/* BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info;
73/* int notify_filter;
74/*
75/* int bounce_original(fp, bounce_info, headers_only)
76/* VSTREAM *fp;
77/* BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info;
78/* int headers_only;
79/*
80/* void bounce_delrcpt(bounce_info)
81/* BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info;
82/*
83/* void bounce_delrcpt_one(bounce_info)
84/* BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info;
85/* DESCRIPTION
86/* This module implements the grunt work of sending a non-delivery
87/* notification. A bounce is sent in a form that satisfies RFC 1894
88/* (delivery status notifications).
89/*
90/* bounce_mail_init() bundles up its argument and attempts to
91/* open the corresponding logfile and message file. A BOUNCE_INFO
92/* structure contains all the necessary information about an
93/* undeliverable message.
94/*
95/* bounce_mail_one_init() provides the same function for only
96/* one recipient that is not read from bounce logfile.
97/*
98/* bounce_mail_free() releases memory allocated by bounce_mail_init()
99/* and closes any files opened by bounce_mail_init().
100/*
101/* bounce_header() produces a standard mail header with the specified
102/* recipient and starts a text/plain message segment for the
103/* human-readable problem description. postmaster_copy is either
104/* POSTMASTER_COPY or NO_POSTMASTER_COPY.
105/*
106/* bounce_boilerplate() produces the standard "sorry" text that
107/* creates the illusion that mail systems are civilized.
108/*
109/* bounce_recipient_log() sends a human-readable representation of
110/* logfile information for one recipient, with the recipient address
111/* and with the text why the recipient was undeliverable.
112/*
113/* bounce_diagnostic_log() sends a human-readable representation of
114/* logfile information for all undeliverable recipients. The
115/* notify_filter specifies what recipient status records should be
116/* reported: DSN_NOTIFY_SUCCESS, DSN_NOTIFY_FAILURE, DSN_NOTIFY_DELAY.
117/* In the absence of DSN NOTIFY information all records are reported.
118/* The result value is -1 in case of error, the number of reported
119/* recipients in case of success.
120/*
121/* bounce_header_dsn() starts a message/delivery-status message
122/* segment and sends the machine-readable information that identifies
123/* the reporting MTA.
124/*
125/* bounce_recipient_dsn() sends a machine-readable representation of
126/* logfile information for one recipient, with the recipient address
127/* and with the text why the recipient was undeliverable.
128/*
129/* bounce_diagnostic_dsn() sends a machine-readable representation of
130/* logfile information for all undeliverable recipients. The
131/* notify_filter specifies what recipient status records should be
132/* reported: DSN_NOTIFY_SUCCESS, DSN_NOTIFY_FAILURE, DSN_NOTIFY_DELAY.
133/* In the absence of DSN NOTIFY information all records are reported.
134/* The result value is -1 in case of error, the number of reported
135/* recipients in case of success.
136/*
137/* bounce_original() starts a message/rfc822 or text/rfc822-headers
138/* message segment and sends the original message, either full
139/* (DSN_RET_FULL) or message headers only (DSN_RET_HDRS).
140/*
141/* bounce_delrcpt() deletes recipients in the logfile from the original
142/* queue file.
143/*
144/* bounce_delrcpt_one() deletes one recipient from the original
145/* queue file.
146/* DIAGNOSTICS
147/* Fatal error: error opening existing file.
148/* BUGS
149/* SEE ALSO
150/* bounce(3) basic bounce service client interface
151/* LICENSE
152/* .ad
153/* .fi
154/* The Secure Mailer license must be distributed with this software.
155/* AUTHOR(S)
156/* Wietse Venema
157/* IBM T.J. Watson Research
158/* P.O. Box 704
159/* Yorktown Heights, NY 10598, USA
160/*--*/

213/* bounce_mail_alloc - initialize */
214
215static BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_mail_alloc(const char *service,
216 const char *queue_name,
217 const char *queue_id,
218 const char *encoding,
219 int smtputf8,
220 const char *dsn_envid,
221 RCPT_BUF *rcpt_buf,
222 DSN_BUF *dsn_buf,
223 BOUNCE_TEMPLATE *template,
224 BOUNCE_LOG *log_handle)
225{
226 BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info;
227 int rec_type;
228
229 /*
230 * Bundle up a bunch of parameters and initialize information that will
231 * be discovered on the fly.
232 *
233 * XXX Instead of overriding the returned-message MIME encoding, separate
234 * the returned-message MIME encoding from the (boiler plate, delivery
235 * status) MIME encoding.
236 */
237 bounce_info = (BOUNCE_INFO *) mymalloc(sizeof(*bounce_info));
238 bounce_info->service = service;
239 bounce_info->queue_name = queue_name;
240 bounce_info->queue_id = queue_id;
241 bounce_info->smtputf8 = smtputf8;
242 /* Fix 20140708: override MIME encoding: addresses may be 8bit. */
243 /* Fix 20140718: override MIME encoding: 8bit $myhostname expansion. */
244 if (var_smtputf8_enable /* was: bounce_info->smtputf8 */ ) {
245 bounce_info->mime_encoding = "8bit";
246 } else if (strcmp(encoding, MAIL_ATTR_ENC_8BIT) == 0) {
247 bounce_info->mime_encoding = "8bit";
248 } else if (strcmp(encoding, MAIL_ATTR_ENC_7BIT) == 0) {
249 bounce_info->mime_encoding = "7bit";
250 } else {
251 if (strcmp(encoding, MAIL_ATTR_ENC_NONE) != 0)
252 msg_warn("%s: unknown encoding: %.200s",
253 bounce_info->queue_id, encoding);
254 bounce_info->mime_encoding = 0;
255 }
256 if (dsn_envid && *dsn_envid)
257 bounce_info->dsn_envid = dsn_envid;
258 else
259 bounce_info->dsn_envid = 0;
260 bounce_info->template = template;
261 bounce_info->buf = vstring_alloc(100);
262 bounce_info->sender = vstring_alloc(100);
263 bounce_info->arrival_time = 0;
264 bounce_info->orig_offs = 0;
265 bounce_info->message_size = 0;
266 bounce_info->rcpt_buf = rcpt_buf;
267 bounce_info->dsn_buf = dsn_buf;
268 bounce_info->log_handle = log_handle;
269
270 /*
271 * RFC 1894: diagnostic-type is an RFC 822 atom. We use X-$mail_name and
272 * must ensure it is valid.
273 */
274 bounce_info->mail_name = mystrdup(var_mail_name);
275 translit(bounce_info->mail_name, " \t\r\n()<>@,;:\\\".[]",
276 "-----------------");
277
278 /*
279 * Compute a supposedly unique boundary string. This assumes that a queue
280 * ID and a hostname contain acceptable characters for a boundary string,
281 * but the assumption is not verified.
282 */
283 vstring_sprintf(bounce_info->buf, "%s.%lu/%s",
284 queue_id, (unsigned long) event_time(), var_myhostname);
285 bounce_info->mime_boundary = mystrdup(STR(bounce_info->buf));
286
287 /*
288 * If the original message cannot be found, do not raise a run-time
289 * error. There is nothing we can do about the error, and all we are
290 * doing is to inform the sender of a delivery problem. Bouncing a
291 * message does not have to be a perfect job. But if the system IS
292 * running out of resources, raise a fatal run-time error and force a
293 * backoff.
294 */
295 if ((bounce_info->orig_fp = mail_queue_open(queue_name, queue_id,
296 O_RDWR, 0)) == 0
297 && errno != ENOENT)
298 msg_fatal("open %s %s: %m", service, queue_id);
299
300 /*
301 * Get time/size/sender information from the original message envelope
302 * records. If the envelope is corrupted just send whatever we can
303 * (remember this is a best effort, it does not have to be perfect).
304 *
305 * Lock the file for shared use, so that queue manager leaves it alone after
306 * restarting.
307 */
308#define DELIVER_LOCK_MODE (MYFLOCK_OP_SHARED | MYFLOCK_OP_NOWAIT)
309
310 if (bounce_info->orig_fp != 0) {
311 if (myflock(vstream_fileno(bounce_info->orig_fp), INTERNAL_LOCK,
312 DELIVER_LOCK_MODE) < 0)
313 msg_fatal("cannot get shared lock on %s: %m",
314 VSTREAM_PATH(bounce_info->orig_fp));
315 while ((rec_type = rec_get(bounce_info->orig_fp,
316 bounce_info->buf, 0)) > 0) {
317
318 /*
319 * Postfix version dependent: data offset in SIZE record.
320 */
321 if (rec_type == REC_TYPE_SIZE) {
322 if (bounce_info->message_size == 0)
323 sscanf(STR(bounce_info->buf), "%ld %ld",
324 &bounce_info->message_size,
325 &bounce_info->orig_offs);
326 if (bounce_info->message_size < 0)
327 bounce_info->message_size = 0;
328 if (bounce_info->orig_offs < 0)
329 bounce_info->orig_offs = 0;
330 }
331
332 /*
333 * Information for the Arrival-Date: attribute.
334 */
335 else if (rec_type == REC_TYPE_TIME) {
336 if (bounce_info->arrival_time == 0
337 && (bounce_info->arrival_time = atol(STR(bounce_info->buf))) < 0)
338 bounce_info->arrival_time = 0;
339 }
340
341 /*
342 * Information for the X-Postfix-Sender: attribute.
343 */
344 else if (rec_type == REC_TYPE_FROM) {
345 quote_822_local_flags(bounce_info->sender,
346 VSTRING_LEN(bounce_info->buf) ?
347 STR(bounce_info->buf) :
348 mail_addr_mail_daemon(), 0);
349 }
350
351 /*
352 * Backwards compatibility: no data offset in SIZE record.
353 */
354 else if (rec_type == REC_TYPE_MESG) {
355 /* XXX Future: sender+recipient after message content. */
356 if (VSTRING_LEN(bounce_info->sender) == 0)
357 msg_warn("%s: no sender before message content record",
358 bounce_info->queue_id);
359 bounce_info->orig_offs = vstream_ftell(bounce_info->orig_fp);
360 break;
361 }
362 if (bounce_info->orig_offs > 0
363 && bounce_info->arrival_time > 0
364 && VSTRING_LEN(bounce_info->sender) > 0)
365 break;
366 }
367 }
368 return (bounce_info);
369}

371/* bounce_mail_init - initialize */
372
373BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_mail_init(const char *service,
374 const char *queue_name,
375 const char *queue_id,
376 const char *encoding,
377 int smtputf8,
378 const char *dsn_envid,
379 BOUNCE_TEMPLATE *template)
380{
381 BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info;
382 BOUNCE_LOG *log_handle;
383 RCPT_BUF *rcpt_buf;
384 DSN_BUF *dsn_buf;
385
386 /*
387 * Initialize the bounce_info structure. If the bounce log cannot be
388 * found, do not raise a fatal run-time error. There is nothing we can do
389 * about the error, and all we are doing is to inform the sender of a
390 * delivery problem, Bouncing a message does not have to be a perfect
391 * job. But if the system IS running out of resources, raise a fatal
392 * run-time error and force a backoff.
393 */
394 if ((log_handle = bounce_log_open(service, queue_id, O_RDONLY, 0)) == 0) {
395 if (errno != ENOENT)
396 msg_fatal("open %s %s: %m", service, queue_id);
397 rcpt_buf = 0;
398 dsn_buf = 0;
399 } else {
400 rcpt_buf = rcpb_create();
401 dsn_buf = dsb_create();
402 }
403 bounce_info = bounce_mail_alloc(service, queue_name, queue_id, encoding,
404 smtputf8, dsn_envid, rcpt_buf, dsn_buf,
405 template, log_handle);
406 return (bounce_info);
407}

409/* bounce_mail_one_init - initialize */
410
411BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_mail_one_init(const char *queue_name,
412 const char *queue_id,
413 const char *encoding,
414 int smtputf8,
415 const char *dsn_envid,
416 RCPT_BUF *rcpt_buf,
417 DSN_BUF *dsn_buf,
418 BOUNCE_TEMPLATE *template)
419{
420 BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info;
421
422 /*
423 * Initialize the bounce_info structure for just one recipient.
424 */
425 bounce_info = bounce_mail_alloc("none", queue_name, queue_id, encoding,
426 smtputf8, dsn_envid, rcpt_buf, dsn_buf,
427 template, (BOUNCE_LOG *) 0);
428 return (bounce_info);
429}

431/* bounce_mail_free - undo bounce_mail_init */
432
433void bounce_mail_free(BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info)
434{
435 if (bounce_info->log_handle) {
436 if (bounce_log_close(bounce_info->log_handle))
437 msg_warn("%s: read bounce log %s: %m",
438 bounce_info->queue_id, bounce_info->queue_id);
439 rcpb_free(bounce_info->rcpt_buf);
440 dsb_free(bounce_info->dsn_buf);
441 }
442 if (bounce_info->orig_fp && vstream_fclose(bounce_info->orig_fp))
443 msg_warn("%s: read message file %s %s: %m",
444 bounce_info->queue_id, bounce_info->queue_name,
445 bounce_info->queue_id);
446 vstring_free(bounce_info->buf);
447 vstring_free(bounce_info->sender);
448 myfree(bounce_info->mail_name);
449 myfree((void *) bounce_info->mime_boundary);
450 myfree((void *) bounce_info);
451}

453/* bounce_header - generate bounce message header */
454
455int bounce_header(VSTREAM *bounce, BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info,
456 const char *dest, int postmaster_copy)
457{
458 BOUNCE_TEMPLATE *template = bounce_info->template;
459
460 /*
461 * Print a minimal bounce header. The cleanup service will add other
462 * headers and will make all addresses fully qualified.
463 */
464#define STREQ(a, b) (strcasecmp((a), (b)) == 0)
465#define STRNE(a, b) (strcasecmp((a), (b)) != 0)
466
467 /*
468 * Generic headers.
469 */
470 bounce_template_headers(post_mail_fprintf, bounce, template,
471 STR(quote_822_local(bounce_info->buf, dest)),
472 postmaster_copy);
473
474 /*
475 * Auto-Submitted header, as per RFC 3834.
476 */
477 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Auto-Submitted: %s", postmaster_copy ?
478 "auto-generated" : "auto-replied");
479
480 /*
481 * MIME header. Use 8bit encoding when either the bounced message or the
482 * template requires it.
483 */
484 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "MIME-Version: 1.0");
485 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Content-Type: %s; report-type=%s;",
486 "multipart/report", "delivery-status");
487 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "\tboundary=\"%s\"", bounce_info->mime_boundary);
488 if (bounce_info->mime_encoding)
489 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Content-Transfer-Encoding: %s",
490 STREQ(bounce_info->mime_encoding, MAIL_ATTR_ENC_7BIT) ?
491 bounce_template_encoding(template) :
492 bounce_info->mime_encoding);
493 post_mail_fputs(bounce, "");
494 post_mail_fputs(bounce, "This is a MIME-encapsulated message.");
495
496 /*
497 * MIME header.
498 */
499#define NOT_US_ASCII(tp) \
500 STRNE(bounce_template_charset(template), "us-ascii")
501
502#define NOT_7BIT_MIME(bp) \
503 (bp->mime_encoding && STRNE(bp->mime_encoding, MAIL_ATTR_ENC_7BIT))
504
505 post_mail_fputs(bounce, "");
506 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "--%s", bounce_info->mime_boundary);
507 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Content-Description: %s", "Notification");
508 /* Fix 20140718: UTF-8 address or $myhostname expansion. */
509 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Content-Type: %s; charset=%s",
510 "text/plain", NOT_US_ASCII(template) ?
511 bounce_template_charset(template) :
512 NOT_7BIT_MIME(bounce_info) ?
513 "utf-8" : "us-ascii");
514 /* Fix 20140709: addresses may be 8bit. */
515 if (NOT_7BIT_MIME(bounce_info))
516 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Content-Transfer-Encoding: %s",
517 bounce_info->mime_encoding);
518 post_mail_fputs(bounce, "");
519
520 return (vstream_ferror(bounce));
521}

535/* bounce_print - line_wrap callback */
536
537static void bounce_print(const char *str, int len, int indent, void *context)
538{
539 VSTREAM *bounce = (VSTREAM *) context;
540
541 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "%*s%.*s", indent, "", len, str);
542}
543
544/* bounce_print_wrap - print and wrap a line */
545
546static void bounce_print_wrap(VSTREAM *bounce, BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info,
547 const char *format,...)
548{
549 va_list ap;
550
551#define LENGTH 79
552#define INDENT 4
553
554 va_start(ap, format);
555 vstring_vsprintf(bounce_info->buf, format, ap);
556 va_end(ap);
557 line_wrap(STR(bounce_info->buf), LENGTH, INDENT,
558 bounce_print, (void *) bounce);
559}

561/* bounce_recipient_log - send one bounce log report entry */
562
563int bounce_recipient_log(VSTREAM *bounce, BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info)
564{
565 RECIPIENT *rcpt = &bounce_info->rcpt_buf->rcpt;
566 DSN *dsn = &bounce_info->dsn_buf->dsn;
567
568 /*
569 * Mask control and non-ASCII characters (done in bounce_log_read()),
570 * wrap long lines and prepend one blank, so this data can safely be
571 * piped into other programs. Sort of like TCP Wrapper's safe_finger
572 * program.
573 */
574#define NON_NULL_EMPTY(s) ((s) && *(s))
575
576 post_mail_fputs(bounce, "");
577 if (NON_NULL_EMPTY(rcpt->orig_addr)) {
578 bounce_print_wrap(bounce, bounce_info, "<%s> (expanded from <%s>): %s",
579 rcpt->address, rcpt->orig_addr, dsn->reason);
580 } else {
581 bounce_print_wrap(bounce, bounce_info, "<%s>: %s",
582 rcpt->address, dsn->reason);
583 }
584 return (vstream_ferror(bounce));
585}
586
587/* bounce_diagnostic_log - send bounce log report */
588
589int bounce_diagnostic_log(VSTREAM *bounce, BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info,
590 int notify_filter)
591{
592 RECIPIENT *rcpt = &bounce_info->rcpt_buf->rcpt;
593 int count = 0;
594
595 /*
596 * Append a human-readable copy of the delivery error log. We're doing a
597 * best effort, so there is no point raising a fatal run-time error in
598 * case of a logfile read error.
599 *
600 * XXX DSN If the logfile with failed recipients is unavailable, pretend
601 * that we found something anyway, so that this notification will not be
602 * canceled.
603 */
604 if (bounce_info->log_handle == 0
605 || bounce_log_rewind(bounce_info->log_handle)) {
606 if (IS_FAILURE_TEMPLATE(bounce_info->template)) {
607 post_mail_fputs(bounce, "");
608 post_mail_fputs(bounce, "\t--- Delivery report unavailable ---");
609 count = 1; /* XXX don't abort */
610 }
611 } else {
612 while (bounce_log_read(bounce_info->log_handle, bounce_info->rcpt_buf,
613 bounce_info->dsn_buf) != 0) {
614 if (rcpt->dsn_notify == 0 /* compat */
615 || (rcpt->dsn_notify & notify_filter)) {
616 count++;
617 if (bounce_recipient_log(bounce, bounce_info) != 0)
618 break;
619 }
620 }
621 }
622 return (vstream_ferror(bounce) ? -1 : count);
623}
624
625/* bounce_header_dsn - send per-MTA bounce DSN records */
626
627int bounce_header_dsn(VSTREAM *bounce, BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info)
628{
629
630 /*
631 * MIME header.
632 */
633 post_mail_fputs(bounce, "");
634 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "--%s", bounce_info->mime_boundary);
635 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Content-Description: %s",
636 "Delivery report");
637 /* Generate *global* only if the original requested SMTPUTF8 support. */
638 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Content-Type: message/%sdelivery-status",
639 (bounce_info->smtputf8 & SMTPUTF8_FLAG_REQUESTED) ?
640 "global-" : "");
641 /* Fix 20140709: addresses may be 8bit. */
642 if (NOT_7BIT_MIME(bounce_info))
643 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Content-Transfer-Encoding: %s",
644 bounce_info->mime_encoding);
645
646 /*
647 * According to RFC 1894: The body of a message/delivery-status consists
648 * of one or more "fields" formatted according to the ABNF of RFC 822
649 * header "fields" (see [6]). The per-message fields appear first,
650 * followed by a blank line.
651 */
652 post_mail_fputs(bounce, "");
653 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Reporting-MTA: dns; %s", var_myhostname);
654#if 0
655 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Received-From-MTA: dns; %s", "whatever");
656#endif
657 if (NON_NULL_EMPTY(bounce_info->dsn_envid)) {
658 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Original-Envelope-Id: %s",
659 bounce_info->dsn_envid);
660 }
661 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "X-%s-Queue-ID: %s",
662 bounce_info->mail_name, bounce_info->queue_id);
663
664#define IS_UTF8_ADDRESS(str, len) \
665 ((str)[0] != 0 && !allascii(str) && valid_utf8_string((str), (len)))
666
667 /* Fix 20140708: use "utf-8" or "rfc822" as appropriate. */
668 if (VSTRING_LEN(bounce_info->sender) > 0)
669 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "X-%s-Sender: %s; %s",
670 bounce_info->mail_name, bounce_info->smtputf8
671 && IS_UTF8_ADDRESS(STR(bounce_info->sender),
672 VSTRING_LEN(bounce_info->sender)) ?
673 "utf-8" : "rfc822", STR(bounce_info->sender));
674 if (bounce_info->arrival_time > 0)
675 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Arrival-Date: %s",
676 mail_date(bounce_info->arrival_time));
677 return (vstream_ferror(bounce));
678}
679
680/* bounce_recipient_dsn - send per-recipient DSN records */
681
682int bounce_recipient_dsn(VSTREAM *bounce, BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info)
683{
684 RECIPIENT *rcpt = &bounce_info->rcpt_buf->rcpt;
685 DSN *dsn = &bounce_info->dsn_buf->dsn;
686
687 post_mail_fputs(bounce, "");
688 /* Fix 20140708: Don't send "utf-8" type with non-UTF8 address. */
689 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Final-Recipient: %s; %s",
690 bounce_info->smtputf8
691 && IS_UTF8_ADDRESS(rcpt->address,
692 strlen(rcpt->address)) ?
693 "utf-8" : "rfc822", rcpt->address);
694
695 /*
696 * XXX DSN
697 *
698 * RFC 3464 section 6.3.d: "If no ORCPT parameter was provided for this
699 * recipient, the Original-Recipient field MUST NOT appear."
700 *
701 * This is inconsistent with section 5.2.1.d: "If no ORCPT parameter was
702 * present in the RCPT command when the message was received, an ORCPT
703 * parameter MAY be added to the RCPT command when the message is
704 * relayed.". Postfix adds an ORCPT parameter under these conditions.
705 *
706 * Therefore, all down-stream MTAs will send DSNs with Original-Recipient
707 * field ontaining this same ORCPT value. When a down-stream MTA can use
708 * that information in their DSNs, it makes no sense that an up-stream
709 * MTA can't use that same information in its own DSNs.
710 *
711 * Postfix always reports an Original-Recipient field, because it is more
712 * more useful and more consistent.
713 */
714 if (NON_NULL_EMPTY(rcpt->dsn_orcpt)) {
715 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Original-Recipient: %s", rcpt->dsn_orcpt);
716 } else if (NON_NULL_EMPTY(rcpt->orig_addr)) {
717 /* Fix 20140708: Don't send "utf-8" type with non-UTF8 address. */
718 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Original-Recipient: %s; %s",
719 bounce_info->smtputf8
720 && IS_UTF8_ADDRESS(rcpt->orig_addr,
721 strlen(rcpt->orig_addr)) ?
722 "utf-8" : "rfc822", rcpt->orig_addr);
723 }
724 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Action: %s",
725 IS_FAILURE_TEMPLATE(bounce_info->template) ?
726 "failed" : dsn->action);
727 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Status: %s", dsn->status);
728 if (NON_NULL_EMPTY(dsn->mtype) && NON_NULL_EMPTY(dsn->mname))
729 bounce_print_wrap(bounce, bounce_info, "Remote-MTA: %s; %s",
730 dsn->mtype, dsn->mname);
731 if (NON_NULL_EMPTY(dsn->dtype) && NON_NULL_EMPTY(dsn->dtext))
732 bounce_print_wrap(bounce, bounce_info, "Diagnostic-Code: %s; %s",
733 dsn->dtype, dsn->dtext);
734 else
735 bounce_print_wrap(bounce, bounce_info, "Diagnostic-Code: X-%s; %s",
736 bounce_info->mail_name, dsn->reason);
737#if 0
738 if (dsn->time > 0)
739 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Last-Attempt-Date: %s",
740 mail_date(dsn->time));
741#endif
742 if (IS_DELAY_TEMPLATE(bounce_info->template))
743 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Will-Retry-Until: %s",
744 mail_date(bounce_info->arrival_time + var_max_queue_time));
745 return (vstream_ferror(bounce));
746}
747
748/* bounce_diagnostic_dsn - send bounce log report, machine readable form */
749
750int bounce_diagnostic_dsn(VSTREAM *bounce, BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info,
751 int notify_filter)
752{
753 RECIPIENT *rcpt = &bounce_info->rcpt_buf->rcpt;
754 int count = 0;
755
756 /*
757 * Append a machine-readable copy of the delivery error log. We're doing
758 * a best effort, so there is no point raising a fatal run-time error in
759 * case of a logfile read error.
760 *
761 * XXX DSN If the logfile with failed recipients is unavailable, pretend
762 * that we found something anyway, so that this notification will not be
763 * canceled.
764 */
765 if (bounce_info->log_handle == 0
766 || bounce_log_rewind(bounce_info->log_handle)) {
767 if (IS_FAILURE_TEMPLATE(bounce_info->template))
768 count = 1; /* XXX don't abort */
769 } else {
770 while (bounce_log_read(bounce_info->log_handle, bounce_info->rcpt_buf,
771 bounce_info->dsn_buf) != 0) {
772 if (rcpt->dsn_notify == 0 /* compat */
773 || (rcpt->dsn_notify & notify_filter)) {
774 count++;
775 if (bounce_recipient_dsn(bounce, bounce_info) != 0)
776 break;
777 }
778 }
779 }
780 return (vstream_ferror(bounce) ? -1 : count);
781}
782
783/* bounce_original - send a copy of the original to the victim */
784
785int bounce_original(VSTREAM *bounce, BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info,
786 int headers_only)
787{
788 int status = 0;
789 int rec_type = 0;
790
791 /*
792 * When truncating a large message, don't damage the MIME structure: send
793 * the message headers only.
794 */
795 if (var_bounce_limit > 0
796 && bounce_info->orig_fp
797 && (bounce_info->message_size <= 0
798 || bounce_info->message_size > var_bounce_limit))
799 headers_only = DSN_RET_HDRS;
800
801 /*
802 * MIME headers.
803 */
804#define IS_UNDELIVERED_TEMPLATE(template) \
805 (IS_FAILURE_TEMPLATE(template) || IS_DELAY_TEMPLATE(template))
806
807 post_mail_fputs(bounce, "");
808 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "--%s", bounce_info->mime_boundary);
809 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Content-Description: %s%s",
810 IS_UNDELIVERED_TEMPLATE(bounce_info->template) ?
811 "Undelivered " : "",
812 headers_only == DSN_RET_HDRS ?
813 "Message Headers" : "Message");
814 /* Generate *global* only if the original requested SMTPUTF8 support. */
815 if (bounce_info->smtputf8 & SMTPUTF8_FLAG_REQUESTED)
816 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Content-Type: message/%s",
817 headers_only == DSN_RET_HDRS ?
818 "global-headers" : "global");
819 else
820 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Content-Type: %s",
821 headers_only == DSN_RET_HDRS ?
822 "text/rfc822-headers" : "message/rfc822");
823 if (NOT_7BIT_MIME(bounce_info))
824 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Content-Transfer-Encoding: %s",
825 bounce_info->mime_encoding);
826 post_mail_fputs(bounce, "");
827
828 /*
829 * Send place holder if original is unavailable.
830 */
831 if (bounce_info->orig_offs == 0 || vstream_fseek(bounce_info->orig_fp,
832 bounce_info->orig_offs, SEEK_SET) < 0) {
833 post_mail_fputs(bounce, "\t--- Undelivered message unavailable ---");
834 return (vstream_ferror(bounce));
835 }
836
837 /*
838 * XXX The cleanup server removes Return-Path: headers. This should be
839 * done only with mail that enters via a non-SMTP channel, but changing
840 * this now could break other software. Removing Return-Path: could break
841 * digital signatures, though this is unlikely. In any case,
842 * header_checks are more effective when the Return-Path: header is
843 * present, so we prepend one to the bounce message.
844 */
845 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "Return-Path: <%s>", STR(bounce_info->sender));
846
847 /*
848 * Copy the original message contents. We're doing raw record output here
849 * so that we don't throw away binary transparency yet.
850 */
851#define IS_HEADER(s) (IS_SPACE_TAB(*(s)) || is_header(s))
852
853 while (status == 0 && (rec_type = rec_get(bounce_info->orig_fp, bounce_info->buf, 0)) > 0) {
854 if (rec_type != REC_TYPE_NORM && rec_type != REC_TYPE_CONT)
855 break;
856 if (headers_only == DSN_RET_HDRS
857 && !IS_HEADER(vstring_str(bounce_info->buf)))
858 break;
859 status = (REC_PUT_BUF(bounce, rec_type, bounce_info->buf) != rec_type);
860 }
861
862 /*
863 * Final MIME headers. These require -- at the end of the boundary
864 * string.
865 *
866 * XXX This should be a separate bounce_terminate() entry so we can be
867 * assured that the terminator will always be sent.
868 */
869 post_mail_fputs(bounce, "");
870 post_mail_fprintf(bounce, "--%s--", bounce_info->mime_boundary);
871
872 return (status);
873}
874
875/* bounce_delrcpt - delete recipients from original queue file */
876
877void bounce_delrcpt(BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info)
878{
879 RECIPIENT *rcpt = &bounce_info->rcpt_buf->rcpt;
880
881 if (bounce_info->orig_fp != 0
882 && bounce_info->log_handle != 0
883 && bounce_log_rewind(bounce_info->log_handle) == 0)
884 while (bounce_log_read(bounce_info->log_handle, bounce_info->rcpt_buf,
885 bounce_info->dsn_buf) != 0)
886 if (rcpt->offset > 0)
887 deliver_completed(bounce_info->orig_fp, rcpt->offset);
888}
889
890/* bounce_delrcpt_one - delete one recipient from original queue file */
891
892void bounce_delrcpt_one(BOUNCE_INFO *bounce_info)
893{
894 RECIPIENT *rcpt = &bounce_info->rcpt_buf->rcpt;
895
896 if (bounce_info->orig_fp != 0 && rcpt->offset > 0)
897 deliver_completed(bounce_info->orig_fp, rcpt->offset);
898}
